e%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20and%20terms%20apply%20to%20offers%20listed%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Credit%20cards%20correspondent%20Katherine%20Fan%20looks%20out%20the%20window%20on%20a%20flight%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673f7514fa0140cdd564b475%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221632%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20your%20flight%20is%20oversold%2C%20your%20airline%20may%20ask%20for%20volunteers%20to%20give%20up%20their%20seats.%20Here's%20what%20to%20know%20about%20getting%20compensation.%3Cp%3EKatherine%20Fan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20ago%20in%20New%20Orleans%2C%20I%20boarded%20a%20flight%20headed%20for%20Austin%2C%20my%20hometown.%20A%20few%20minutes%20before%20our%20scheduled%20departure%20time%2C%20a%20gate%20agent%20came%20back%20on%20board%20to%20tell%20us%20our%20flight%20was%20over%20capacity%2C%20and%20asked%20for%20one%20volunteer%20who%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20stay%20overnight%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20free%20hotel%20night%20and%20a%20%241%2C600%20travel%20voucher.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20hand%20was%20in%20the%20air%20before%20she%20finished%20her%20statement%2C%20and%20I%20quickly%20gathered%20my%20bags%20to%20follow%20her%20off%20the%20plane.%20After%20a%20lot%20of%20back%20and%20forth%20on%20the%20phone%2C%20agents%20at%20the%20gate%20rebooked%20me%20on%20a%20direct%20flight%20for%20the%20following%20day%20and%20gave%20me%20%242%2C500%20in%20travel%20credit%20instead%20of%20the%20original%20%241%2C600.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20why%20they%20increased%20the%20offer%20amount%2C%20but%20I'm%20certainly%20not%20complaining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20frequently%20travel%20alone%2C%20almost%20never%20check%20a%20bag%2C%20and%20usually%20plan%20ahead%20for%20travel%20delays%2C%20so%20I%20often%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20flexibility%20regarding%20when%20and%20how%20I%20get%20from%20Point%20A%20to%20Point%20B.%20I%20highly%20value%20future%20travel%20credit%2C%20and%20don't%20mind%20changing%20my%20plans%20last%20minute%20when%20my%20schedule%20allows%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20I've%20received%20travel%20credit%20in%20exchange%20for%20taking%20a%20later%20flight%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20happens%20more%20often%20than%20you%20might%20think.%20This%20summer%2C%20a%20woman%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-passenger-overbooked-flight-italy-travel-vouchers-2024-8%5C%22%3E%243%2C550%20in%20overbooked%20flight%20vouchers%20from%20American%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20staying%20three%20additional%20nights%20in%20Italy%20on%20the%20airline's%20dime.%20And%20in%202018%2C%20a%20traveler%20famously%20received%20a%20%24%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-gives-10000-voucher-to-bumped-passenger-2018-3%5C%22%3E10%2C000%20United%20voucher%20in%20compensation%20for%20being%20bumped%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20her%20basic%20economy%20seat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20get%20compensation%20for%20giving%20up%20your%20seat%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20get%20travel%20credit%20or%20compensation%20for%20giving%20up%20your%20seat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeak%20travel%20season%20often%20coincides%20with%20flight%20snafus%20from%20inclement%20weather%20or%20mechanical%20issues.%20As%20the%20holidays%20approach%2C%20you%20may%20find%20yourself%20in%20a%20similar%20situation%20to%20mine.%20If%20your%20schedule%20can%20accommodate%20a%20spontaneous%20change%20of%20plans%2C%20here's%20what%20you%20should%20know%20about%20volunteering%20for%20travel%20credit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EUnderstanding%20bumping%20and%20denied%20boarding%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOperating%20a%20commercial%20flight%20is%20expensive%2C%20so%20most%20airlines%20slightly%20oversell%20each%20flight%20to%20compensate%20for%20no-shows%20and%20last-minute%20cancellations.%20The%20complex%20logistics%20typically%20work%20out%2C%20and%20most%20travelers%20board%20the%20flights%20they%20book%20with%20no%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20airlines%20end%20up%20with%20more%20passengers%20than%20available%20seats%20on%20a%20plane.%20In%20my%20case%2C%20for%20example%2C%20most%20of%20the%20travelers%20on%20my%20plane%20had%20been%20rebooked%20from%20a%20previous%20flight%20that%20was%20canceled%20due%20to%20storms%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20flight%20has%20too%20many%20passengers%2C%20someone%20has%20to%20go%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20(DoT)%20has%20strict%20regulations%20on%20how%20airlines%20must%20compensate%20affected%20customers.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Findividuals%2Faviation-consumer-protection%2Fbumping-oversales%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAviation%20consumer%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%20guidelines%20state%20that%20airlines%20must%20first%20ask%20for%20volunteers%20before%20forcing%20anyone%20to%20give%20up%20their%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Travelers%20can%20negotiate%20compensation%5C%22%3ETravelers%20can%20negotiate%20compensation%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%20can%20offer%20any%20amount%20of%20money%20or%20travel%20credit%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20inconvenience%2C%20and%20travelers%20who%20volunteer%20their%20seats%20can%20negotiate%20with%20the%20airline%20for%20what%20they%20want.%20Whether%20you'll%20get%20what%20you%20want%20depends%20on%20how%20much%20the%20airline%20needs%20your%20seat%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20the%20offer%20is%20open%20to%20all%20travelers%20until%20the%20airline's%20needs%20are%20met.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DoT%20recommends%20keeping%20the%20following%20questions%20in%20mind%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhat's%20the%20next%20available%20nonstop%20flight%20with%20a%20confirmed%20seat%3F%20If%20the%20next%20option%20available%20already%20has%20a%20full%20standby%20list%2C%20you%20may%20end%20up%20delayed%20again%20without%20further%20compensation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECan%20the%20airline%20offer%20additional%20amenities%20such%20as%20free%20food%2C%20housing%2C%20and%20transit%20from%20the%20airport%20to%20the%20hotel%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20you%20receive%20a%20travel%20voucher%20instead%20of%20cash%20compensation%2C%20when%20does%20the%20credit%20expire%3F%20Does%20the%20credit%20have%20any%20blackout%20dates%20or%20restrictions%20on%20holiday%20or%20peak%20season%20travel%3F%20And%20can%20you%20use%20the%20credit%20for%20international%20trips%20or%20first-class%20tickets%2C%20or%20are%20you%20limited%20to%20economy-class%20fares%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Decide%20if%20the%20reward%20is%20worth%20the%20hassle%5C%22%3EKeep%20track%20of%20any%20expenses%20for%20future%20reimbursement%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20still%20incur%20some%20expenses%20along%20the%20way%2C%20even%20if%20the%20airline%20has%20offered%20to%20cover%20your%20hotel%20and%20meals.%20In%20my%20situation%2C%20the%20airline%20gave%20me%20the%20wrong%20documents%20for%20my%20hotel%20voucher%2C%20which%20meant%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20own%20room%20upfront%20using%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-credit-cards-travel-insurance%5C%22%3Ecredit%20cards%20with%20travel%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20request%20money%20back%20after%20I%20got%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20checked%20bags%2C%20you%20may%20not%20see%20them%20for%20some%20time%20if%20you%20volunteer%20your%20seat%20since%20your%20luggage%20was%20probably%20loaded%20onto%20your%20original%20flight.%20You'll%20usually%20need%20to%20make%20do%20with%20what%20you%20already%20have%20with%20you%2C%20although%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20purchase%20small%20toiletries%20and%20necessities%20such%20as%20toothpaste%20and%20socks%20and%20claim%20reimbursement%20from%20the%20airline%20later%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-travel-rewards-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ebest%20travel%20rewards%20credit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20offer%20trip%20delay%20benefits%20for%20incidentals%20when%20you're%20delayed%20on%20a%20flight%20you%20bought%20with%20the%20card.%20However%2C%20these%20perks%20may%20not%20apply%20if%20you%20voluntarily%20give%20up%20your%20seat%2C%20so%20check%20with%20the%20credit%20card%20company%20(or%20be%20willing%20to%20pay%20for%20your%20expenses%20out%20of%20pocket)%20before%20going%20on%20a%20shopping%20spree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Decide%20if%20the%20reward%20is%20worth%20the%20hassle%5C%22%3EDecide%20if%20the%20reward%20is%20worth%20the%20hassle%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20also%20consider%20your%20own%20situation%20before%20succumbing%20to%20the%20temptation%20of%20a%20four-figure%20travel%20voucher.%20If%20you%20need%20to%20be%20somewhere%20on%20time%2C%20there's%20no%20guarantee%20that%20another%20flight%20will%20get%20you%20to%20your%20destination%20by%20your%20personal%20deadline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20not%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20give%20up%20your%20seat%20if%20you're%20traveling%20with%20someone%20else%2C%20particularly%20if%20they%20are%20underage%2C%20elderly%2C%20or%20have%20special%20needs.%20Even%20if%20the%20airline%20compensates%20both%20of%20you%20for%20the%20loss%20of%20your%20seats%2C%20it%20may%20be%20hard%20to%20get%20on%20another%20flight%20where%20you%20can%20be%20seated%20together%20or%20enjoy%20the%20same%20benefits%20you%20would%20have%20had%20on%20your%20original%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EYou%20may%20be%20able%20to%20volunteer%20directly%20within%20the%20airline%20app%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAsking%20for%20volunteers%20at%20the%20gate%20%E2%80%94%20or%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20like%20in%20my%20case%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20a%20time-consuming%20process%2C%20so%20some%20airlines%20have%20begun%20streamlining%20the%20process%20by%20contacting%20travelers%20directly.%20If%20you've%20ever%20checked%20in%20for%20a%20flight%20via%20the%20airline's%20app%2C%20you%20may%20have%20been%20invited%20to%20choose%20a%20different%20flight%20at%20no%20additional%20charge%2C%20or%20offered%20the%20chance%20to%20volunteer%20your%20seat%20at%20several%20different%20price%20points.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20know%20if%20you're%20involuntarily%20denied%20boarding%5C%22%3EIf%20you're%20involuntarily%20denied%20boarding%2C%20here's%20what%20to%20know%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20rare%20cases%2C%20you%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20give%20up%20your%20seat%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20volunteer.%20This%20is%20called%20involuntarily%20denied%20boarding%2C%20and%20airlines%20have%20a%20legal%20right%20to%20do%20so%20when%20seats%20are%20oversold.%20However%2C%20the%20airline%20must%20tell%20you%20why%20it%20is%20involuntarily%20denying%20you%20boarding%20and%20must%20provide%20a%20written%20statement%20explaining%20your%20rights%20and%20describing%20how%20it%20decides%20who%20will%20be%20bumped%20from%20the%20flight.%20In%20the%20example%20of%20the%202018%20woman%20who%20received%20%2410%2C000%20from%20United%2C%20for%20example%2C%20she%20was%20bumped%20because%20she%20had%20the%20lowest-class%20fare%20among%20all%20of%20the%20travelers%20on%20the%20plane.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22It%20never%20hurts%20to%20ask%20for%20compensation%5C%22%3EYou're%20not%20always%20eligible%20for%20compensation%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20doesn't%20hurt%20to%20ask%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20been%20involuntarily%20denied%20boarding%2C%20you%20aren't%20automatically%20entitled%20to%20travel%20credit%20or%20a%20refund%20just%20because%20you've%20been%20removed%20from%20a%20flight.%20Airlines%20do%20not%20need%20to%20compensate%20travelers%20who%20are%20denied%20boarding%20due%20to%20safety%2C%20security%2C%20or%20health%20risks%2C%20or%20to%20passengers%20who%20engage%20in%20obscene%2C%20disruptive%2C%20or%20unlawful%20behavior.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DoT%20also%20doesn't%20require%20airlines%20to%20compensate%20travelers%20if%20they%20are%20denied%20boarding%20due%20to%20aircraft%20changes%2C%20weight%20and%20balance%20issues%2C%20or%20downgrades%20in%20fare%20class%20on%20flights%20departing%20from%20non-U.S.%20locations%2C%20charter%20flights%2C%20or%20small%20aircraft%20carrying%2030%20or%20fewer%20passengers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20you%20can%20always%20contact%20the%20airline%20for%20compensation%2C%20even%20if%20they%20aren't%20mandated%20to%20reimburse%20you.%20The%20best%20way%20to%20do%20so%20is%20to%20contact%20the%20airline's%20customer%20service%20team%20after%20your%20travel%20is%20complete.%20You%20can%20typically%20find%20the%20right%20form%20under%20the%20%26quot%3BContact%20Us%26quot%3B%20section%20of%20the%20airline's%20website.%20You'll%20get%20the%20fastest%20response%20if%20you%20include%20your%20date(s)%20of%20travel%2C%20flight%20number(s)%2C%20full%20contact%20information%2C%20and%20airline%20frequent%20flyer%20number.%20I've%20personally%20gotten%20the%20best%20results%20by%20being%20extremely%20polite%2C%20concisely%20stating%20the%20facts%2C%20and%20asking%20for%20exactly%20what%20I%20want.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20thrilled%20with%20the%20compensation%20I%20received%2C%20which%20is%20enough%20to%20allow%20me%20to%20see%20friends%20and%20family%20for%20free%20in%20months%20to%20come.%20If%20you%20have%20the%20misfortune%20of%20being%20on%20an%20oversold%20flight%20this%20season%2C%20consider%20the%20situation%20an%20opportunity%20to%20plan%20future%20adventures%20on%20your%20airline's%20dime.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-airline-voucher-volunteering-seat-on-flight-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732292365000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673f75079f2901eb60362a71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-airline-voucher-volunteering-seat-on-flight-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Holiday%20travels%20often%20coincide%20with%20inclement%20weather.%20If%20your%20flight%20is%20overbooked%2C%20you%20may%20be%20compensated%20if%20you're%20willing%20to%20take%20a%20later%20flight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherinefan%40gmail.com%20(Katherine%20Fan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-airline-voucher-volunteering-seat-on-flight-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cryptos%20targeted%20by%20regulation%20are%20soaring%20on%20SEC%20chair's%20plan%20to%20step%20down%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225037%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gary%20Gensler%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20SEC.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb07b2d17aa3c7b2b3c22c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222519%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGary%20Gensler%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20SEC.%3Cp%3EEvelyn%20Hockstein%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETokens%20in%20the%20crosshairs%20of%20the%20SEC%20are%20rallying%20after%20chairman%20Gary%20Gensle