A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-do-drop-sets-workout-build-muscle-faster-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20muscle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndre%20Adams%2C%20a%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sports%20Medicine%20Master%20trainer%2C%20competes%20in%20the%20International%20Federation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-muscle-according-to-pro-bodybuilder-sadik-hadzovic-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBodybuilding%3C%2Fa%3E%20pro%20league.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20taking%20even%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20warm-up%20and%20working%20in%20a%20few%20sets%20of%20moderate%20weight%20can%20translate%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimprove-mobility-build-muscle-longevity-exercise-personal-trainer-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetter%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20especially%20important%20for%20anyone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stay-fit-exercise-desk-job-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehitting%20the%20gym%20after%20working%20at%20a%20desk%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%20sitting%20all%20day%20can%20create%20tension%20and%20muscle%20imbalances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSkipping%20a%20warm-up%20is%20way%20more%20common%20that%20you%20think.%20I've%20been%20guilty%20of%20it%20too%2C%20everyone's%20on%20a%20time%20crunch%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20lengthy%2C%20it%20can%20be%20five%20minutes%2C%20it's%20just%20performing%20the%20right%20movements%20for%20the%20workout.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f374e31c-a559-4bc3-a7cc-647c08f8a872%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20quick%20four-part%20warm-up%20includes%20foam%20rolling%20and%20body%20weight%20exercise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20typically%20spends%20about%20five%20minutes%20warming%20up%20with%20muscle%20activations%2C%20followed%20by%20five%20minutes%20of%20light%20cardio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJumping%20right%20into%20a%20workout%20can%20increase%20risk%20of%20injury%2C%20which%20may%20not%20happen%20right%20away%20but%20can%20build%20up%20over%20time%2C%20causing%20persistent%20aches%20and%20pains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20warm-up%20is%20also%20important%20to%20prepare%20the%20muscles%20and%20joints%20to%20work%20effectively%20so%20you%20can%20maintain%20the%20highest%20quality%20movement%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20younger%20and%20my%20body%20was%20much%20more%20resilient%20I%20would%20often%20times%20skip%20warm-ups%20all%20together%20and%20get%20away%20with%20it.%20However%2C%20over%20time%20as%20I%20aged%20this%20lead%20to%20pain%2C%20muscle%20imbalances%2C%20unproductive%20workouts%20and%20ultimately%20injuries%20and%20setbacks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222656%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bodybuilder%20Andre%20Adams%20on%20stage%20at%20a%20competition%20with%20the%20IFBB%20pro%20league%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67409b20fa0140cdd564dd0a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221771%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndre%20Adams%20competes%20in%20the%20International%20Federation%20of%20Bodybuilding%20pro%20league.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Andre%20Adams%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20he%20warms%20up%20by%20following%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.nasm.org%2Fces%2Fa-guide-to-nasms-corrective-exercise-continuum%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20steps%20recommended%20by%20the%20NASM%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInhibit%20%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20first%20step%20is%20to%20reduce%20tension%20and%20calm%20down%20overactive%20or%20tight%20muscles%2C%20usually%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fbenefits-of-foam-rolling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efoam%20