0significantly%20enhance%20training%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20study%20author%20Igor%20Nasser%2C%20professor%20at%20the%20Federal%20University%20of%20Rio%20de%20Janeiro%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIn%20our%20study%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20the%20strategy%20of%20applying%20greater%20intensity%20during%20the%20warm-up%20sets%20leads%20to%20better%20outcomes%20than%20using%20lighter%20loads%2C%20which%20is%20more%20commonly%20practiced.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20confirms%20what%20bodybuilders%20already%20know%20%E2%80%94%20that%20not%20going%20heavy%20enough%20on%20the%20warm-up%20can%20leave%20gains%20on%20the%20table%2C%20according%20to%20Adams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20haven't%20activated%20as%20much%20muscle%20fiber%20as%20you%20could%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20going%20all-out.%20Adams%20said%20for%20a%20working%20weight%20of%20200%20pounds%2C%20a%20warm-up%20might%20involve%20one%20set%20at%20100%20pounds%2C%20following%20by%20a%20set%20at%20150%20pounds%20before%20the%20main%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20the%20time%20for%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20process%20only%20adds%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20a%20workout%2C%20and%20can%20boost%20performance%2C%20improve%20range%20of%20motion%2C%20and%20prevent%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20making%20the%20muscle%20fibers%20activate%2C%20it's%20making%20the%20body%20work%20as%20a%20system%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20we%20have%20to%20do%20those%20four%20steps%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbodybuilder-shares-5-minute-warmup-with-weights-better-gains-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732289261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673e2084ede4eeae3928a21c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbodybuilder-sha