ution%20and%20the%20stubble%20burning%20by%20farmers%20in%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana.%20While%20the%20Central%20Air%20Quality%20Management%20(CAQM)%2C%20the%20pollution%20control%20body%2C%20has%20appreciated%20Punjab%20for%20significantly%20bringing%20down%20the%20cases%20of%20stubble%20burning%20in%20the%20state%2C%20scientist%20Hiren%20Jethva%20at%20NASA%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Centre%2C%20differs%20and%20told%20NDTV%20that%20farmers%20are%20timing%20stubble%20burning%20with%20NASA%20satellites%20overpass%20time%20over%20the%20subcontinent%20leading%20to%20severe%20undercounting.%20Now%2C%20exclusive%20satellite%20images%20accessed%20by%20NDTV%20appear%20to%20confirm%20the%20inference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESatellite%20Images%20Of%20Punjab%20Farm%20Fires%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENDTV%20accessed%20satellite%20images%20of%20a%20small%20area%20west%20of%20Amritsar%2C%20to%20understand%20the%20extent%20of%20farm%20fires%20on%20November%2018%20at%202%3A18%20pm.%20It%20may%20look%20like%20an%20image%20of%20a%20warzone%2C%20but%20the%20smoke%20is%20not%20from%20the%20impact%20of%20bombs%20but%20from%20farmers%20burning%20their%20agriculture%20stubble.%20The%20red%20circles%20indicate%20the%20location%20of%20farm%20fires%20in%20a%20small%20area%20lying%20west%20of%20the%20Amritsar%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20satellite%20imagery%20experts%20consulted%20by%20NDTV%2C%20counted%20at%20least%2026%20independent%20farm%20fires%20in%20the%20north%20and%20west%20of%20Amritsar%20on%20November%2018%2C%20shortly%20after%20NASA's%20satellites%20with%20fire-detecting%20sensors%20had%20completed%20their%20overpass%20of%20the%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22High%20res%20here%20%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22High%20res%20here%20%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Ffvhkmkbo_maxar_625x300_22_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20single%20farm%20fire%20emanates%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20smoke.%20High%20res%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fhn7bpse8_maxar-farm-fires_625x300_22_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20zoomed-in%20image%20of%20a%20farm%20fire%20west%20of%20Amristar%20airport%20shows%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20smoke%20emanating%20from%20a%20single%20farm%20fire%20that%20burns%20for%20several%20hours%2C%20contributing%20significantly%20to%20poor%20air%20quality%20and%20lowering%20the%20visibility%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2018%2C%20flight%20operations%20at%20Amritsar%20Airport%20were%20impacted%20due%20to%20poor%20visibility%20as%20a%20result%20of%20smog%20and%20the%20smoke%20from%20farm%20fires%20has%20converted%20the%20Indo-Gangetic%20plain%20belt%20which%20includes%20Delhi%20and%20its%20adjoining%20areas%20into%20a%20gas%20chamber.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20more%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-exclusive-wary-of-nasa-satellites-how-farmers-in-punjab-time-crop-burning-scientist-explains-7021591%5C%22%3EExclusive%3A%20Wary%20Of%20NASA%20Satellites%2C%20How%20Farmers%20In%20Punjab%20Time%20Crop-Burning%2C%20Scientist%20Explains%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jethva%2C%20earlier%20told%20NDTV%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20overpass%20time%20of%20NASA%20satellites%20over%20the%20region%20is%20around%201%3A30-2%3A00%20pm%20but%20somehow%20they%20(farmers)%20have%20learnt%20that%20they%20can%20bypass%20the%20satellite%20overpass%20time%20and%20can%20burn%20the%20crop%20residue%20in%20the%20late%20afternoon.%20This%20is%20confirmed%20by%20the%20South%20Korean%20geostationary%20satellite%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20crop%20burning%20happens%20after%202%20pm%20once%20the%20NASA%20satellites%20overpass%20the%20region%20when%20there%20is%20no%20surveillance%2C%20but%20the%20fires%20cannot%20be%20hidden%20from%20geostationary%20satellites%20which%20take%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20region%20every%20five%20minutes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20images%20accessed%20by%20NDTV%20were%20captured%20at%202%3A18%20pm%20and%20farm%20fires%20were%20visible%20in%20the%20Maxar%20imagery%20and%20are%20absent%20from%20farm%20fire%20data%20processed%20by%20Sumoi-NPP%2FVIIRS%20sensors%20used%20by%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20satellite%20captures%20an%20image%20of%20an%20area%20adjacent%20to%20the%20spot%20where%20a%20single%20fire%20emanated%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20smoke.%20At%20least%20eight%20independent%20farm%20fires%20were%20spotted%20by%20experts%20who%20were%20consulted%20by%20NDTV%20to%20locate%20the%20incidents%20of%20stubble%20burning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22High%20res%20here%20%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22High%20res%20here%20%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F4l2gn68g_maxar-farm-fire_625x300_22_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20eight%20spots%20were%20identified%20where%20fire%20fires%20took%20place%20on%20Nov%2018.%20High%20res%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F4l2gn68g_maxar-farm-fire_625x300_22_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jethva%20earlier%20in%20an%20X%20post%2C%20shared%20satellite%20images%20from%20October%2029%2C%20taken%20by%20the%20GEO-KOMSAT%20A2%20satellite%2C%20showing%20a%20timelapse%20of%20the%20crop-burning%20activities%20in%20northwest%20India.%20The%20images%20show%20dense%20cloud%20cover%20over%20the%20region%20post-4%20pm%2C%20when%20compared%20to%201%3A30%20pm%2C%20suggesting%20that%20farmers%20are%20burning%20crops%20late%20afternoon%20to%20avoid%20NASA%20satellite%20surveillance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENASA%20Data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20yellow%20box%20next%20to%20Amristar%20is%20the%20location%20of%20the%20satellite%20images%20accessed%20by%20NDTV.%20The%20red%20dots%20are%20farm%20fires%20which%20have%20been%20detected%20by%20sensors%20from%20NASA%20World%20View%2C%20data%20from%20which%20is%20extensively%20used%20in%20India.%C2%A0The%20fire%20sensor%20data%20was%20taken%20at%202%3A18%20pm%20on%20November%2018%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%20when%20other%20satellites%2C%20except%20NASA's%2C%20passed%20over%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22High%20res%20here%20%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22High%20res%20here%20%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fk0i00v3o_nasa-active-fire-data_625x300_22_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20Worldview%20data%20from%20November%2018%20at%202%3A18%20pm%20after%20satellites%20overpass.%20High%20res%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fk0i00v3o_nasa-active-fire-data_625x300_22_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20images%20appear%20to%20confirm%20that%20there%20is%20a%20severe%20undercount%20of%20farm%20fires%20in%20Punjab%20which%20contribute%20significantly%20to%20the%20air%20pollution%20load%20this%20time%20of%20the%20year%20when%20farmers%20burn%20their%20agriculture%20stubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jethva%20earlier%20told%20NDTV%2C%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20farmers%20can%20hide%20the%20crop%20burning%20from%20the%201%3A30%20pm%20overpass%20time%20but%20the%20PM%202.5%20data%20and%20the%20pollution%20load%20over%20the%20Indo-Gangetic%20plain%20region%2C%20the%20geostationary%20satellite%20data%20and%20the%20burnt...everything%20is%20pointing%20toward%20fire%20is%20still%20present.%20Smog%20towers%20are%20a%20small%20fix.%20It%20won't%20work%20unless%20we%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20crop%20burning%20in%20the%20region.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThermal%20Inversion%20-%20Another%20Key%20Factor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThermal%20inversion%20is%20a%20big%20factor%20behind%20the%20sudden%20spike%20in%20dense%20smog%20and%20pollution%20levels.%20Mr%20Jethva%20explained%20that%20%26quot%3BThe%20warmer%20air%20sits%20above%20the%20cooler%20air%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20that%20does%20not%20allow%20the%20vertical%20mixing%20of%20pollutants%20and%20whatever%20we%20emit%20at%20the%20surface%20stays%20for%20around%20200%20metres%20within%20the%20boundary%20layer.%20The%20stronger%20the%20thermal%20inversion%2C%20the%20more%20pollutants%20will%20be%20trapped%20near%20the%20surface%20because%20there%20is%20no%20venting%20place%20for%20the%20pollutants%20to%20go%20up%20in%20the%20vertical%20direction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20satellite%20images%2C%20we%20can%20notice%20that%20smoke%20from%20crop%20burning%20is%20mixed%20with%20clouds%20or%20is%20above%20them%20and%20that%20kind%20of%20situation%20furthers%20thermal%20inversion%20because%20of%20the%20absorption%20of%20light-absorbing%20aerosols%20and%20that%20it%20further%20warms%20the%20upper%20layer%20and%20increases%20thermal%20inversion%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jethva%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20particulate%20matter%20(PM)%20acts%20as%20a%20cloud%20condensation%20nuclei%20which%20favours%20the%20formation%20of%20fog%20and%20when%20temperatures%20go%20down%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20aerosols%20contribute%20to%20fog%20formation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fembed-player%2F%3Fsite%3Dclassic%26id%3D864083%26autostart%3Dfalse%26autoplay%3D0%26pWidth%3D500%26pHeight%3D281%26category%3Dembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732284000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fiujmp43g_maxar-farm-fires_625x300_22_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhas-there-been-a-major-undercount-of-punjab-farm-fires-what-satellite-pics-show-7080200%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20and%20its%20adjoining%20areas%20are%20covered%20in%20smog%20and%20air%20quality%20is%20still%20in%20