ppearance%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20said%20the%20strike%20on%20the%20city%20of%20Dnipro%20had%20tested%20in%20combat%20conditions%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20newest%20Russian%20mid-range%20missile%20systems%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20missile%20engineers%20had%20christened%20the%20missile%20Oreshnik%2C%20or%20hazel%20tree%20in%20Russian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20said%20it%20had%20been%20deployed%20%26quot%3Bin%20a%20non-nuclear%20hypersonic%20configuration%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Btest%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20successful%20and%20had%20hit%20its%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpeed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20defences%20cannot%20intercept%20the%20Oreshnik%2C%20which%20attacks%20at%20a%20speed%20of%20Mach%2010%2C%20or%202.5-3%20kilometres%20per%20second%2C%20Putin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHypersonic%20missiles%20travel%20at%20speeds%20of%20at%20least%20Mach%205%20--%20five%20times%20the%20speed%20of%20sound%20--%20and%20can%20manoeuvre%20mid-flight%2C%20making%20them%20harder%20to%20track%20and%20intercept.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BModern%20air%20defence%20systems...%20cannot%20intercept%20such%20missiles.%20That's%20impossible%2C%26quot%3B%20Putin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20of%20today%20there%20are%20no%20means%20of%20counteracting%20such%20a%20weapon%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20president%20boasted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWarheads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Oreshnik%20missile%20could%20have%20three%20to%20six%20warheads%2C%20military%20expert%20Viktor%20Baranets%20wrote%20in%20the%20Komsomolskaya%20Pravda%20tabloid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIgor%20Korotchenko%2C%20editor%20of%20the%20Moscow-based%20National%20Defence%20journal%2C%20told%20TASS%20state%20news%20agency%20that%20based%20on%20video%20footage%20of%20the%20strike%2C%20Oreshnik%20has%20multiple%20independently%20guided%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%20they%20were%20conventional%2C%20but%20it%20could%20also%20carry%20nuclear%20warheads%2C%20military%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bpractically%20simultaneous%20arrival%20of%20the%20warheads%20at%20the%20target%26quot%3B%20shows%20the%20system%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20effective%26quot%3B%2C%20Korotchenko%20said%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bmasterpiece%20of%20modern%20Russian%20solid-fuel%20military%20missile%20construction%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERange%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20missile%20was%20reported%20by%20Ukrainian%20media%20to%20have%20been%20fired%20from%20the%20Kapustin%20Yar%20range%20in%20the%20Astrakhan%20region%2C%20around%20900%20kilometres%20(550%20miles)%20from%20Dnipro.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20described%20the%20missile%20in%20Russian%20as%20%26quot%3Bmedium-range%26quot%3B%20but%20Russian%20military%20experts%20said%20the%20English%20term%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bintermediate-range%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20intermediate-range%20ballistic%20missile%20(IRBM)%20has%20a%20range%20of%201%2C000-5%2C500%20kilometres%2C%20a%20level%20below%20that%20of%20an%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20(ICBM).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilitary%20expert%20Ilya%20Kramnik%20told%20Izvestia%20newspaper%20that%20Oreshnik's%20range%20could%20be%20at%20the%20top%20end%20of%20intermediate%2C%20around%203%2C000%20-%205%2C000%20kilometres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20any%20case%20we%20witnessed%20the%20first%20combat%20use%20in%20history%20by%20Russia%20of%20an%20intermediate-range%20missile%2C%26quot%3B%20Dmitry%20Kornev%2C%20editor%20of%20Military%20Russia%20website%2C%20told%20Izvestia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOrigins%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20described%20Oreshnik%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bexperimental%26quot%3B%20missile%20based%20on%20Russia's%20RS-26%20Rubezh%20ICBM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELittle%20is%20known%20about%20Rubezh%2C%20a%20modification%20of%20Topol%20ICBM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETASS%20state%20news%20agency%20reported%2C%20citing%20a%20source%2C%20in%202018%20that%20development%20of%20Rubezh%20was%20frozen%20under%20the%20state%20weapons%20programme%20up%20to%202027%2C%20to%20prioritise%20another%20system%2C%20Avangard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20weapons%20expert%20Yan%20Matveyev%20wrote%20on%20Telegram%20that%20Oreshnik%20probably%20had%20two%20stages%20and%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bquite%20expensive%26quot%3B%2C%20heavy%20and%20not%20mass-produced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThreat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20range%20means%20%26quot%3BOreshnik%20can%20threaten%20practically%20all%20of%20Europe%26quot%3B%20but%20not%20the%20United%20States%2C%20weapons%20expert%20Pavel%20Podvig%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Russian%20Nuclear%20Forces%20Project%2C%20told%20Russian%20Telegram%20channel%20Ostorozhno%20Novosti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%201987%20signed%20a%20treaty%20agreeing%20to%20give%20up%20all%20use%20of%20missiles%20with%20a%20range%20of%20500%20to%205%2C500%20kilometres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Washington%20and%20Moscow%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Intermediate-Range%20Nuclear%20Forces%20Treaty%20in%202019%2C%20each%20accusing%20the%20other%20of%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20said%20Thursday%20that%20Russia%20will%20%26quot%3Baddress%20the%20question%20of%20further%20deployment%20of%20intermediate%20and%20shorter-range%20missiles%20based%20on%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20its%20satellites%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732277220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F0ftmou98_russia-missile-attack_625x300_22_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2