ade%20it%20tough%20for%20the%20seeds%20to%20survive%20in%20adverse%20climatic%20regions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20seeds%20give%20quantity%20but%20not%20quality%2C%E2%80%9D%20Darlapudi%20says.%20%E2%80%9CInstead%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Edesi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(local%20varieties)%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehave%20two%20important%20qualities%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20sustain%20natural%20calamities%20and%20give%20a%C2%A0good%20aroma.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20he%20says%2C%20sets%20them%20apart%20from%20hybridised%20varieties.%20The%20first%20step%20of%20seed%20preservation%20is%20seed%20collection.%20%E2%80%9CI%20chose%20tribal%20areas%20that%20do%20not%20get%20much%20water%2C%20aside%20from%20a%20few%20hours%20of%20rainfall.%20This%20creates%20drought-resistant%20seeds.%20I%20collected%20seeds%20from%20the%20Pottangi%20area%20in%20Odisha%2C%20the%20Dantewada%20area%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Seethampeta%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20Velur%20in%20Kerala.%20These%20include%20seeds%20of%20medicinal%20value%20and%20paddy%20varieties.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20collection%2C%20Darlapudi%20uses%20a%20varied%20array%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F189462%2Fdebal-deb-seed-bank-conserves-native-rice-variety-inspiring-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreservation%20methods%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20range%20from%20potting%20the%20seed%20in%20mud%20or%20a%20bamboo%20container%20or%20applying%20soil%20to%20the%20seed%20and%20keeping%20it%20in%20the%20shade.%20But%20one%20of%20his%20favourite%20methods%20is%20coating%20the%20seed%20with%20ash.%20%E2%80%9CSome%20varieties%20like%20pumpkin%20or%20creepers%20come%20with%20slurry%20inside.%20Ash%20from%20burning%20dried%20cow%20dung%20is%20applied%20to%20the%20seeds%20and%20they%20are%20kept%20in%20bamboo%20containers%20or%20mud%20pots.%20This%20ash%20acts%20as%20a%20layer%20of%20protection%20for%20the%20seeds%